gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 117, Suns 107
gameRecap.excerpt: Boston avoids their first three-game losing streak of the season as they defeat Phoenix, 117-107. For Boston, Jayson Tatum (29 points (five 3PM), 10 rebounds, seven assists) and Jaylen Brown (27 points, three assists, two steals) combine for 56 PTS to lead the way in the victory. Kevin Durant finished with a season-high 45 points (four 3PM), 10 rebounds, and six rebounds with Bradley Beal recording 25 points, four assists, and three steals for Phoenix in the losing effort. Boston improves to 49-14 on the season, while Phoenix moves to 37-27 with the loss.
